{
  "message": "fuzz(ext4-checksums): 20 structured seeds across every parser/verifier\nentry point\n\nfuzz_ext4_checksums runs every checksum + parsing routine in\nffs_ondisk on arbitrary bytes (Ext4GroupDesc::parse_from_bytes \u00d7\ndesc_size 32/64, Ext4Superblock::parse_superblock_region,\nverify_inode_checksum / verify_dir_block_checksum /\nverify_extent_block_checksum / verify_group_desc_checksum,\nExt4Inode::parse_from_bytes + parse_inode_extent_tree +\nparse_ibody_xattrs, block_bitmap_checksum_value /\ninode_bitmap_checksum_value, verify_*_bitmap_free_count, dx_hash for\nhash_version 0..5+255, lookup_in_dir_block + casefold,\niter_dir_block \u00d7 block_size 1024/2048/4096). Existing 6 ad-hoc seeds\ncovered byte / dir_basic / inode_132 / inode_256 / random / empty\nbut never the 32-byte vs 64-byte group-descriptor split or the\nfeature-flag matrix.\n\nAdds 20 seeds spanning every parser/verifier entry point:\n\n  Group descriptors:\n  * 32-byte (legacy) descriptor with bitmap addresses, free counts,\n    flags, and lo-half csums populated\n  * 64-byte descriptor with hi-half fields populated\n\n  Superblocks (1024-byte regions):\n  * minimal valid SB (magic + log_block_size=4K + 64-byte desc)\n  * SB with metadata_csum incompat flag set\n  * SB with 32-byte descriptor (no 64bit feature)\n  * SB with 1K blocks (log_block_size=0)\n  * SB with bad magic (parser must reject early)\n\n  Inodes:\n  * 256-byte regular file with extra_isize=32\n  * 128-byte (small inode, no extras)\n  * 256-byte with EXTENTS_FL flag set + valid 0xF30A extent header\n    in i_block (drives parse_inode_extent_tree)\n\n  Directory blocks:\n  * 4K block with \".\" + \"..\" root entries (proper rec_len chain)\n  * 4K block with multiple entries (file_a.txt + sub_dir)\n  * 4K block with `test_file` and `Test_File` matches for\n    lookup_in_dir_block + casefold lookup\n  * 2K block with \".\" + \"..\" entries\n\n  Bitmaps (1024 bytes = 8192 bits):\n  * all-zero (8192 free)\n  * all-0xFF (0 free)\n  * alternating 0xAA pattern (50% free)\n\n  Tiny inputs to drive every parser's \"too-short\" early-error:\n  * 4-byte garbage\n  * 16-byte input for dx_hash across hash_version 0..5+255\n  * 512-byte all-zero block\n\nValidated by an 11 s libFuzzer run: 291k executions over the new\ncorpus, no crashes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
